text: Khalid Al-Estashi (born 19 March 1974) is a Yemeni long-distance runner who competed internationally for Yemen at the 1992 Summer Olympics. ==Career== Al- Estashi was still a teenager when he competed in the 10,000 metres at the 1992 Summer Olympics held in Barcelona, Spain, he finished his heat in 26th place out 28 that started so didn't qualify for the final. ==References== Category:1974 births Category:Living people Category:Yemeni male long-distance runners Category:Olympic athletes of Yemen Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1992 Summer Olympics
title: Khalid Al-Estashi
